				<td colspan="2"><span>I can't decide what I think of monk lull.  In return for it being unresistable, they can basically lull just one mob because the recast timer is longer than the lull duration.
<br />

<br />
Our lull is resistable but with no recast timer so we can lull multiple mobs.
<br />

<br />
My partner in crime is a monk and we're often comparing notes on pulls.  His lull does give him an advantage in some pulls I am still the better puller in others.  
<br />

<br />
For example, we were doing the Tipt Trial in GoD the other day and he started off pulling so I could sing mana song to the cleric in downtime as she was running low.  Once she got up to speed and had attuned her heals to the tank, she wasn't dropping below 80m too often.  Some of the Tipt mobs run incredibly fast but I know they are often buffed by shaman mobs, so I wanted to see if they were sowed or if their speed was innate.  I switched off as puller and was able to get 2 - 4 casts of dispell on the mob before it hit camp which made the mob much easier to handle.  So while the monk and I did an equivalent job of splitting the mobs, I had the added advantage of bringing it in dispelled.  
<br />

<br />
Before the monk lull was introduced, my monk partner would have to have me lull a mob when he split.  It simply gives him the option now to do it solo in some cases.  I haven't seen it in action in LDoN hards yet though.
<br />

<br />
Calli</span></td>
