				<td colspan="2"><span>Our small guild has 2 people in it who are known as the only ones in the guild who can effectively pull hard LDON -- myself and our top monk, Mookane.  From what Mook says, their lull is not resistable, but the refresh time on it basically means they can really only use it to keep one mob from agroing, then rely on FD to split what remains.  He's really really good at utilizing it, but it is not really tremendously overpowered compared to our spotty lull.  It is POSSIBLE (though unlikely) for a bard to lull 2 or 3 and pull one out of a crowded room.  A monk simply cannot do that at all.  At the same time, we have all had mobs that resist lull 4 or 5 times in a row then agro on us and that is never going to happen to a monk.
<br />

<br />
So all in all, I have to say the monk LDON pulling package is different, but about equally effective as ours.  I want my guild to get MORE capable hard LDON pullers so everyone in the guild can enjoy the faster AP accumulation and better drops that my regular group already experiences.</span></td>
