				<td colspan="2"><span>The <i>phantom</i> line of monk abilities shines in raid situations. Typically where a pulling <i>chain</i> is used. No one monk can truely benefit from this ability in a room with more than 3 mobs. Sure its going to be easier to split 2 than it is 3, but a monk isnt getting that big of an advantge.
<br />

<br />
However. In a raid situation where there is a pull team, being able to lull 3 out of 4 almost instantly and single pull the 4th is invaluable. Being able to <b>know</b> that your pull team is only going to bring back one mob in high end encounters is definately reassuring. Pull teams / duo's are common in my case. I dont know too many people who solo pull on raids anymore. Its just that much easier to have someone you are firmiliar with there helping you out.</span></td>
